Mutation burden by age and cell type: mixed effects model regression

loading results of hdp signature analysis (no priors)

groupname = "AX001_KX001_KX002_KX003_TX001_TX002_CB001"
sig_prop_type = read.table("colonyinfo_AX001_KX001_KX002_KX003_TX001_TX002_CB001.txt", header=T, stringsAsFactors = F, sep="\t")
sig_prop_type$AgeFactor = factor(sig_prop_type$Age, levels=c(81,63,38,29,4,0)) 
#sig_prop_type$Nmut_hsc_as_SNVindel = sig_prop_type$Nmut_hsc_as + sig_prop_type$Nmut_hsc_as_indel

mixed effects model regression

library(nlme)
m3Allsub = subset(sig_prop_type, Cell.type2 != "Treg")
full.lymph.Age_cell.interaction.lme <- lme(fixed = Nmut_hsc_as ~ Age * Cell.type2, 
                            random = ~ 1 | Donor / Cell.type2, 
                            weights = varIdent(form= ~ 1 | Cell.type2),
                            data = m3Allsub, method="ML")
summary(full.lymph.Age_cell.interaction.lme)

per cell subset, extract slopes and intercepts (with CIs)

mycelltypes = c( "HSC", "Naive B", "Memory B", "Naive T",  "Memory T")
myintercepts = myslopes = data.frame()
for (i in 1:5){
  m3Allsub_naiveB = m3Allsub
m3Allsub_naiveB$Cell.type2 = factor(m3Allsub_naiveB$Cell.type2, levels=c(mycelltypes[i],mycelltypes[!(1:5 %in% i)]) )
full.lymph.Age_cell.interaction.lme_naiveB <- lme(fixed = Nmut_hsc_as ~ Age * Cell.type2, 
                            random = ~ 1 | Donor / Cell.type2, 
                            weights = varIdent(form= ~ 1 | Cell.type2),
                            data = m3Allsub_naiveB, method="ML")
myfixed = intervals(full.lymph.Age_cell.interaction.lme_naiveB)$fixed
myintercepts[i,1:3] = myfixed[1,]
myslopes[i,1:3] = myfixed[2,]
}
colnames(myslopes) = colnames(myintercepts) = c("lower", "est.","upper")
rownames(myslopes) = rownames(myintercepts) = mycelltypes
#write.table(myintercepts, file="myintercepts.txt", quote=F, sep="\t")
#write.table(myslopes, file="myslopes.txt", quote=F, sep="\t")

## add jitter to the age
m3AllsubShuff_j = m3AllsubShuff
m3AllsubShuff_j$Age = m3AllsubShuff$Age + sample(-2000:2000, size=length(m3AllsubShuff$Age))/1000

colorCodesSet3 = c("#7fc97f", colorCodesSet2[2], "#bc80bd", colorCodesSet2[4],colorCodesSet2[3])
names(colorCodesSet3) = names(colorCodesSet2)[1:5]
hsc_color = colorCodesSet3[1]
#hsc_color = "#a1d99b"
hsc_type = "HSC"
hsc_slope = my_slope[1]    
hsc_intercept = my_yint[1]  

celltypeplots = list()
for (i in 1:4){
  myind = i
  focal_color = colorCodesSet3[myind+1]
  focal_type = names(colorCodesSet3)[myind+1]    
  focal_slope = my_slope[myind+1]    
  focal_intercept = my_yint[myind+1]    
  my_color_type = c("HSC"="black","Naive B"="grey","Memory B"="grey","Naive T"="grey","Memory T"="grey")
  my_fill_type = c("HSC"=as.character(hsc_color), "Naive B"="white","Memory B"="white","Naive T"="white","Memory T"="white")
  my_color_type[i+1] = "black"
  my_fill_type[i+1] = focal_color
  mytitle = c("Naive B (N=85)",  "Memory B (N=74)", "Naive T (N=365)",  "Memory T (N=100)")[myind]
  m3AllsubShuff2 = rbind(subset(m3AllsubShuff_j, Cell.type2!="HSC" & Cell.type2!=focal_type), subset(m3AllsubShuff_j, Cell.type2=="HSC"), subset(m3AllsubShuff_j, Cell.type2==focal_type))

  celltypeplots[[i]] = 
  ggplot(m3AllsubShuff2)+
    geom_abline(intercept=hsc_intercept, slope=hsc_slope, col=hsc_color)+
    geom_abline(intercept=focal_intercept, slope=focal_slope, col=focal_color)+
    geom_point(data = subset(m3AllsubShuff2, Cell.type2!="HSC" & Cell.type2!=focal_type), aes(Age, Nmut_hsc_as), alpha=1, pch=21, cex=2, color="grey", fill="white")+
    geom_point(data = subset(m3AllsubShuff2, Cell.type2=="HSC" | Cell.type2==focal_type), aes(Age, Nmut_hsc_as, col=Cell.type2, fill=Cell.type2), alpha=1, pch=21, cex=2)+
    scale_fill_manual("", values=as.character(my_fill_type[c(1,i+1)]))+
    scale_color_manual("", values=as.character(my_color_type[c(1,i+1)]))+
    ggtitle(mytitle)+
    xlab("Age")+
    ylab("SNVs / cell")+
    ylim(-200,5500)+
    xlim(-7,90)+
    theme_light()+
    theme(legend.position = "none")  
}
p1 = plot_grid(celltypeplots[[1]],celltypeplots[[2]],celltypeplots[[3]],celltypeplots[[4]], nrow=2, scale = 0.95)
